{
  "texts": [
    "They include liquid crystals (LC), MEMS/NOEMS, and phase change materials (PCMs).",
    "LC on silicon (LCOS) tuning for display applications has been demonstrated at a large scale, and LC has also been the technology of choice for freespace wavelength-selective switches.",
    "As phase shifters, they leverage birefringence to demonstrate a strong electro-optic effect.",
    "The alignment of the LC molecules can be controlled by applying electrical voltage (<1 V) without drawing any significant static or dynamic current (nA).",
    "Hence, they consume extremely low power but currently suffer from IL 78, although very low IL has been demonstrated in visible band recently 79."
  ]
}